{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775863568048,"sessionID":"ses_28648f112ffezeBig0vH7hGGOs","part":{"id":"prt_d79b796ae001qtFQ4vedvkOcz4","messageID":"msg_d79b78ee9001XIUsk1Mj3lvsVq","sessionID":"ses_28648f112ffezeBig0vH7hGGOs","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775863570677,"sessionID":"ses_28648f112ffezeBig0vH7hGGOs","part":{"id":"prt_d79b79997001g0KB3eK1eHNJXZ","messageID":"msg_d79b78ee9001XIUsk1Mj3lvsVq","sessionID":"ses_28648f112ffezeBig0vH7hGGOs","type":"text","text":"Now I have a good understanding of the proposal format. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-019 (CLI binary entry points). Based on the context:\n\n1. AR-019 is about creating 4 CLI binaries in the `cmd` module\n2. Currently there's only `cmd/agentd/main.go` (a Kubernetes controller)\n3. The project has `client-go` for interacting with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n4. Following the existing proposal structure","time":{"start":1775863570675,"end":1775863570675}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863693255,"sessionID":"ses_28648f112ffezeBig0vH7hGGOs","part":{"id":"prt_d79b7a0f6001EqeBIssLwGgcHc","messageID":"msg_d79b78ee9001XIUsk1Mj3lvsVq","sessionID":"ses_28648f112ffezeBig0vH7hGGOs","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1c7647cde59d46baa40f32d5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md","content":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements 4 CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project under the `cmd` module. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide standalone CLI tools** - Offer command-line interfaces for interacting with AgentCube resources (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n2. **Enable operational workflows** - Support creation, inspection, modification, and deletion of AgentCube custom resources\n3. **Facilitate debugging and testing** - Provide tools for operators and developers to inspect and troubleshoot AgentCube deployments\n4. **Support automation and scripting** - Enable CI/CD pipelines and operational scripts to interact with AgentCube via CLI\n\nThis implementation builds upon the generated client-go library (`deployment/client-go.md`) and provides user-facing tooling for the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - `agentcube` - Main CLI entry point with subcommands\n  - `agentd` - Kubernetes controller for AgentRuntime reconciliation (already exists)\n  - `picod` - PicoD HTTP daemon for code execution (standalone binary)\n  - `agentcube-admin` - Administrative CLI for cluster-wide operations\n  - Common CLI infrastructure (logging, config, authentication)\n  - Integration with client-go for Kubernetes API interaction\n  - Documentation and usage examples\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - Controller logic implementation (covered in AR-017, AR-018)\n  - PicoD execution engine (covered in AR-015)\n  - Router/authentication service (covered in AR-010, AR-011)\n  - Workload manager controller (covered in other ARs)\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing cmd/ Structure\n\nThe current `cmd/` directory contains:\n\n1. **cmd/agentd/main.go**:\n   - Kubernetes controller using controller-runtime\n   - Reconciles AgentRuntime resources\n   - Supports metrics, health probes, leader election\n   - Uses zap logging, klog integration\n   - Registers with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` scheme\n\n### Gaps Identified\n\n1. **No user-facing CLI** - No tool for operators to interact with AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **No picod binary** - PicoD HTTP daemon not packaged as standalone binary\n3. **No admin tool** - No administrative CLI for cluster-wide operations (cleanup, migration, diagnostics)\n4. **No unified agentcube CLI** - No kubectl-like CLI for AgentCube-specific operations\n\n### Client-Go Context\n\nPer `deployment/client-go.md`, the generated client provides:\n\n- **Clientset** with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` interface\n- **Typed clients** for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter`\n- **Informers** for watching resource changes\n- **Listers** for efficient caching\n- **Fake clients** for testing\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. Binary Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentd/           # Kubernetes controller (existing)\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ picod/            # PicoD HTTP daemon\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentcube/        # Main CLI tool\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.go\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ agentcube-admin/  # Administrative CLI\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.go\n```\n\n### 2. agentd Controller (Existing - Enhancement)\n\nCurrent `cmd/agentd/main.go` provides:\n- Controller-runtime based manager\n- AgentRuntime reconciliation\n- Metrics and health endpoints\n\n**No changes required** - Already functional.\n\n### 3. picod HTTP Daemon\n\n```go\n// cmd/picod/main.go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"flag\"\n    \"net/http\"\n    \"os\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    var (\n        port        int\n        workspace   string\n        authMode    string\n        publicKeyPEM string\n        skipPaths   string\n    )\n    \n    flag.IntVar(&port, \"port\", 8080, \"HTTP server port\")\n    flag.StringVar(&workspace, \"workspace\", \".\", \"Base workspace directory\")\n    flag.StringVar(&authMode, \"auth\", \"none\", \"Authentication mode: picod or none\")\n    flag.StringVar(&publicKeyPEM, \"public-key\", \"\", \"RSA public key (base64-encoded PEM)\")\n    flag.StringVar(&skipPaths, \"skip-paths\", \"/health\", \"Comma-separated paths to skip auth\")\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    // Load configuration\n    config := &picod.Config{\n        Port:         port,\n        Workspace:    workspace,\n        AuthMode:     authMode,\n        PublicKeyPEM: publicKeyPEM,\n        SkipPaths:    strings.Split(skipPaths, \",\"),\n    }\n    \n    // Initialize PicoD\n    sandboxID := os.Getenv(\"SANDBOX_ID\")\n    p := picod.New(sandboxID,\n        picod.WithWorkDir(workspace),\n        picod.WithLimits(picod.DefaultResourceLimits()),\n        picod.WithSecurityOpts(picod.DefaultSecurityOpts()),\n    )\n    \n    // Setup HTTP server with optional JWT middleware\n    server, err := picod.SetupHTTPServer(p, config)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup server: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    klog.Infof(\"starting PicoD on port %d\", port)\n    if err := server.ListenAndServe(); err != nil && err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"server failed: %v\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**CLI flags:**\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-port` | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `-workspace` | `.` | Base workspace directory |\n| `-auth` | `none` | Authentication mode (`picod` or `none`) |\n| `-public-key` | `` | RSA public key (base64-encoded PEM) |\n| `-skip-paths` | `/health` | Comma-separated paths to skip authentication |\n\n### 4. agentcube CLI\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentcube/main.go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"os\"\n    \n    \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n    \"k8s.io/cli-runtime/pkg/genericclioptions\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/cli/agentruntime\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/cli/codeinterpreter\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    rootCmd := NewRootCommand()\n    if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc NewRootCommand() *cobra.Command {\n    cmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"agentcube\",\n        Short: \"AgentCube CLI for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\",\n        Long:  `AgentCube is a CLI tool for interacting with AgentCube custom resources in Kubernetes.`,\n    }\n    \n    // Add subcommands\n    cmd.AddCommand(agentruntime.NewAgentRuntimeCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(codeinterpreter.NewCodeInterpreterCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(versionCmd)\n    cmd.AddCommand(completionCmd)\n    \n    return cmd\n}\n```\n\n**Subcommand structure:**\n\n```bash\nagentcube\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentruntime\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ create    # Create an AgentRuntime\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ get       # Get AgentRuntime details\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ list      # List AgentRuntimes\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ update    # Update an AgentRuntime\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ delete    # Delete an AgentRuntime\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ describe  # Show detailed AgentRuntime info\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ logs      # Stream AgentRuntime logs\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ create    # Create a CodeInterpreter\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ get       # Get CodeInterpreter details\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ list      # List CodeInterpreters\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ update    # Update a CodeInterpreter\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ delete    # Delete a CodeInterpreter\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ describe  # Show detailed CodeInterpreter info\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ logs      # Stream CodeInterpreter logs\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ exec      # Execute command in CodeInterpreter\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ version       # Show version information\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ completion    # Generate shell completion scripts\n```\n\n### 5. agentcube CLI - agentruntime Commands\n\n```go\n// pkg/cli/agentruntime/agentruntime.go\npackage agentruntime\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"encoding/json\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    \n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n)\n\ntype agentRuntimeOptions struct {\n    kubeconfig string\n    namespace  string\n    name       string\n    timeout    time.Duration\n    output     string\n}\n\nfunc NewAgentRuntimeCommand() *cobra.Command {\n    o := &agentRuntimeOptions{}\n    cmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:     \"agentruntime\",\n        Aliases: []string{\"ar\", \"agentruntimes\"},\n        Short:   \"Manage AgentRuntime resources\",\n        Long:    `Create, update, delete, and inspect AgentRuntime custom resources.`,\n    }\n    \n    cmd.PersistentFlags().StringVar(&o.kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Path to kubeconfig file\")\n    cmd.PersistentFlags().StringVarP(&o.namespace, \"namespace\", \"n\", \"default\", \"Kubernetes namespace\")\n    cmd.PersistentFlags().StringVarP(&o.output, \"output\", \"o\", \"table\", \"Output format (table, json, yaml)\")\n    \n    cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeCreateCommand(o))\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeGetCommand(o))\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeListCommand(o))\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeUpdateCommand(o))\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeDeleteCommand(o))\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeDescribeCommand(o))\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeLogsCommand(o))\n    \n    return cmd\n}\n\nfunc (o *agentRuntimeOptions) getClientset() (*versioned.Clientset, error) {\n    config, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", o.kubeconfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n}\n\nfunc NewAgentRuntimeListCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command {\n    cmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:     \"list [NAME]\",\n        Aliases: []string{\"ls\"},\n        Short:   \"List AgentRuntime resources\",\n        RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n            clientset, err := o.getClientset()\n            if err != nil {\n                return err\n            }\n            \n            list, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(o.namespace).List(cmd.Context(), metav1.ListOptions{})\n            if err != nil {\n                return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list AgentRuntimes: %w\", err)\n            }\n            \n            return o.printAgentRuntimeList(list)\n        },\n    }\n    return cmd\n}\n\nfunc (o *agentRuntimeOptions) printAgentRuntimeList(list *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList) error {\n    switch o.output {\n    case \"json\":\n        encoder := json.NewEncoder(os.Stdout)\n        encoder.SetIndent(\"\", \"  \")\n        return encoder.Encode(list)\n    case \"yaml\":\n        data, err := json.Marshal(list)\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        // Convert to YAML\n        yamlData, err := jsonToYAML(data)\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        fmt.Println(string(yamlData))\n        return nil\n    default: // table\n        return printTable(list.Items)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc printTable(items []runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error {\n    // Print header\n    fmt.Printf(\"%-30s %-15s %-10s %-20s\\n\", \"NAME\", \"NAMESPACE\", \"STATUS\", \"CREATED\")\n    fmt.Println(\"----------------------------------------------------------------------\")\n    \n    for _, item := range items {\n        created := item.CreationTimestamp.Format(time.RFC3339)\n        status := string(item.Status.Phase)\n        fmt.Printf(\"%-30s %-15s %-10s %-20s\\n\",\n            item.Name, item.Namespace, status, created)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### 6. agentcube CLI - codeinterpreter Commands\n\n```go\n// pkg/cli/codeinterpreter/codeinterpreter.go\npackage codeinterpreter\n\nimport (\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"os\"\n    \n    \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/remotecommand\"\n    \n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n)\n\nfunc NewCodeInterpreterCommand() *cobra.Command {\n    cmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:     \"codeinterpreter\",\n        Aliases: []string{\"ci\", \"codeinterpreters\"},\n        Short:   \"Manage CodeInterpreter resources\",\n        Long:    `Create, update, delete, and inspect CodeInterpreter custom resources.`,\n    }\n    \n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterCreateCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterGetCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterListCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterUpdateCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterDeleteCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterDescribeCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterLogsCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterExecCommand())\n    \n    return cmd\n}\n\nfunc NewCodeInterpreterExecCommand() *cobra.Command {\n    var kubeconfig, namespace, container string\n    \n    cmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"exec CODEINTERPRETER_NAME -- COMMAND [args...]\",\n        Short: \"Execute a command in a CodeInterpreter\",\n        Long:  `Execute a command inside the PicoD container of a CodeInterpreter.`,\n        RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n            if len(args) < 1 {\n                return fmt.Errorf(\"command is required\")\n            }\n            \n            ciName := args[0]\n            command := args[1:]\n            \n            config, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n            if err != nil {\n                return err\n            }\n            \n            k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n            if err != nil {\n                return err\n            }\n            \n            // Get CodeInterpreter to find pod name\n            clientset, err := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n            if err != nil {\n                return err\n            }\n            \n            ci, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(cmd.Context(), ciName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n            if err != nil {\n                return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get CodeInterpreter: %w\", err)\n            }\n            \n            podName := ci.Status.PodName\n            if podName == \"\" {\n                return fmt.Errorf(\"CodeInterpreter is not running (no pod assigned)\")\n            }\n            \n            // Execute command in pod\n            req := k8sClient.CoreV1().RESTClient().\n                Post().\n                Resource(\"pods\").\n                Name(podName).\n                Namespace(ci.Namespace).\n                SubResource(\"exec\").\n                Param(\"container\", container).\n                Param(\"stdout\", \"true\").\n                Param(\"stderr\", \"true\").\n                Param(\"command\", command[0])\n            \n            for _, arg := range command[1:] {\n                req.Param(\"command\", arg)\n            }\n            \n            executor, err := remotecommand.NewSPDYExecutor(config, \"POST\", req.URL())\n            if err != nil {\n                return err\n            }\n            \n            return executor.Stream(remotecommand.StreamOptions{\n                Stdout: os.Stdout,\n                Stderr: os.Stderr,\n            })\n        },\n    }\n    \n    cmd.Flags().StringVar(&kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Path to kubeconfig file\")\n    cmd.Flags().StringVarP(&namespace, \"namespace\", \"n\", \"default\", \"Kubernetes namespace\")\n    cmd.Flags().StringVar(&container, \"container\", \"picod\", \"Container name\")\n    \n    return cmd\n}\n```\n\n### 7. agentcube-admin CLI\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"os\"\n    \n    \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/admin/cleanup\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/admin/diagnostics\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/admin/migrate\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    rootCmd := NewRootCommand()\n    if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc NewRootCommand() *cobra.Command {\n    cmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"agentcube-admin\",\n        Short: \"AgentCube Administrative CLI\",\n        Long:  `Administrative tool for cluster-wide AgentCube operations.`,\n    }\n    \n    cmd.AddCommand(cleanup.NewCleanupCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(diagnostics.NewDiagnosticsCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(migrate.NewMigrateCommand())\n    cmd.AddCommand(versionCmd)\n    \n    return cmd\n}\n```\n\n**Subcommand structure:**\n\n```bash\nagentcube-admin\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cleanup\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ sandboxes     # Clean up orphaned sandboxes\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ sessions      # Clean up expired sessions\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ resources     # Clean up all orphaned resources\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ diagnostics\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cluster       # Cluster health check\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ sandboxes     # Sandbox diagnostics\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ metrics       # Export metrics\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ migrate\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ v1-to-v2      # Migrate between API versions\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ import        # Import resources from file\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ version           # Show version information\n```\n\n### 8. Common CLI Infrastructure\n\n```go\n// pkg/cli/common/config.go\npackage common\n\nimport (\n    \"os\"\n    \"path/filepath\"\n    \n    \"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/util/homedir\"\n)\n\ntype CLIConfig struct {\n    Kubeconfig string `mapstructure:\"kubeconfig\"`\n    Namespace  string `mapstructure:\"namespace\"`\n    Timeout    int    `mapstructure:\"timeout\"`\n    Output     string `mapstructure:\"output\"`\n    LogLevel   string `mapstructure:\"log-level\"`\n}\n\nfunc LoadConfig() (*CLIConfig, error) {\n    viper.SetConfigName(\"config\")\n    viper.SetConfigType(\"yaml\")\n    \n    // Search in home directory\n    if home := homedir.HomeDir(); home != \"\" {\n        viper.AddConfigPath(filepath.Join(home, \".agentcube\"))\n    }\n    \n    // Search in current directory\n    viper.AddConfigPath(\".\")\n    \n    // Environment variables\n    viper.AutomaticEnv()\n    \n    // Defaults\n    viper.SetDefault(\"kubeconfig\", \"\")\n    viper.SetDefault(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n    viper.SetDefault(\"timeout\", 30)\n    viper.SetDefault(\"output\", \"table\")\n    viper.SetDefault(\"log-level\", \"info\")\n    \n    if err := viper.ReadInConfig(); err != nil {\n        // Config file is optional\n        if _, ok := err.(viper.ConfigFileNotFoundError); !ok {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n    }\n    \n    var config CLIConfig\n    if err := viper.Unmarshal(&config); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    // Override with environment variables\n    if kubeconfig := os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\"); kubeconfig != \"\" {\n        config.Kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n    }\n    \n    return &config, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 9. Version Information\n\n```go\n// pkg/version/version.go\npackage version\n\nvar (\n    Version   = \"0.0.0\"\n    GitCommit = \"unknown\"\n    BuildDate = \"unknown\"\n    GoVersion = \"unknown\"\n)\n\ntype Info struct {\n    Version   string `json:\"version\"`\n    GitCommit string `json:\"gitCommit\"`\n    BuildDate string `json:\"buildDate\"`\n    GoVersion string `json:\"goVersion\"`\n}\n\nfunc Get() Info {\n    return Info{\n        Version:   Version,\n        GitCommit: GitCommit,\n        BuildDate: BuildDate,\n        GoVersion: GoVersion,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 10. Build System\n\n```makefile\n# Makefile additions\n\nBINARIES := agentd picod agentcube agentcube-admin\nOUTPUT_DIR := ./bin\n\n.PHONY: build\nbuild: $(BINARIES)\n\nagentd:\n\tgo build -o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n\npicod:\n\tgo build -o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/picod ./cmd/picod\n\nagentcube:\n\tgo build -ldflags \"-X github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/version.Version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n\t\t-o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n\nagentcube-admin:\n\tgo build -ldflags \"-X github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/version.Version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n\t\t-o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube-admin ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n\n.PHONY: install\ninstall:\n\tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentd $(GOPATH)/bin/\n\tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/picod $(GOPATH)/bin/\n\tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube $(GOPATH)/bin/\n\tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube-admin $(GOPATH)/bin/\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/spf13/cobra` | CLI framework |\n| `github.com/spf13/viper` | Configuration management |\n| `k8s.io/cli-runtime` | Kubernetes CLI utilities |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/utils` | Kubernetes utilities |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client-go |\n| `gopkg.in/yaml.v3` | YAML encoding/decoding |\n\n### Files to Create\n\n```\ncmd/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ picod/\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentcube/\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.go\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ agentcube-admin/\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.go\n\npkg/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cli/\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ common/\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ config.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ flags.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ output.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentruntime/\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentruntime.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ create.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ get.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ list.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ update.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ delete.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ describe.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ logs.go\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter/\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter.go\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ create.go\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ get.go\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ list.go\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ update.go\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ delete.go\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ describe.go\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ logs.go\nŌöé       ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ exec.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ admin/\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cleanup/\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cleanup.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ sandboxes.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ sessions.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ diagnostics/\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ diagnostics.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cluster.go\nŌöé   Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ metrics.go\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ migrate/\nŌöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ migrate.go\nŌöé       ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ import.go\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ version/\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ version.go\n```\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Build System**: Makefile needs to build all 4 binaries\n2. **CI/CD Pipeline**: Need to test and package all binaries\n3. **Documentation**: CLI usage documentation needed\n4. **Release Process**: All binaries should be versioned and released together\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- `agentd` remains unchanged\n- All CLIs are new additions with no existing API surface\n- Configuration files are optional with sensible defaults\n- Kubernetes API compatibility follows client-go version\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| CLI complexity | Low | Low | Follow established patterns (kubectl, helm) |\n| API version drift | Medium | Medium | Pin client-go version, test against multiple K8s versions |\n| Authentication issues | Medium | Medium | Support standard kubeconfig, service account tokens |\n| Resource naming conflicts | Low | Low | Use clear naming conventions, validate resource names |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Multi-purpose Binary\n\n**Approach**: Combine all functionality into a single `agentcube` binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube picod`, etc.)\n\n**Pros**:\n- Single binary to distribute and version\n- Easier to maintain consistent versioning\n- Smaller overall footprint\n\n**Cons**:\n- Larger binary size\n- All components must share dependencies\n- Harder to deploy individual components\n- Controller and CLI have different lifecycle requirements\n\n**Decision**: Separate binaries provide better modularity and deployment flexibility.\n\n### Alternative 2: kubectl Plugin\n\n**Approach**: Implement as `kubectl-agentcube` plugin using kubectl plugin framework\n\n**Pros**:\n- Leverages existing kubectl authentication and context management\n- Familiar UX for Kubernetes users\n- No separate authentication logic needed\n\n**Cons**:\n- Requires kubectl installation\n- Less flexibility for custom operations\n- Harder to distribute and version independently\n- Limited to kubectl plugin capabilities\n\n**Decision**: Standalone CLI provides more flexibility and doesn't require kubectl dependency.\n\n### Alternative 3: Kubernetes kustomize/helm Only\n\n**Approach**: Use only kustomize/helm templates without custom CLI\n\n**Pros**:\n- Standard Kubernetes tooling\n- No custom code to maintain\n- Declarative configuration\n\n**Cons**:\n- No programmatic API for automation\n- Limited runtime operations support\n- No exec/logs/describe functionality\n- Harder to script complex workflows\n\n**Decision**: CLI complements declarative tools by providing imperative operations.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **TestCLIConfig_LoadConfig**: Configuration loading from file/env/flags\n2. **TestAgentRuntimeList_TableOutput**: Table output formatting\n3. **TestAgentRuntimeList_JSONOutput**: JSON output formatting\n4. **TestAgentRuntimeCreate_Validate**: Input validation for create\n5. **TestCodeInterpreterExec_Command**: Command execution in pods\n6. **TestCleanup_OrphanedSandboxes**: Cleanup logic\n7. **TestDiagnostics_ClusterHealth**: Cluster health checks\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **TestAgentRuntime_CRUD**: Full CRUD lifecycle via CLI\n2. **TestCodeInterpreter_CRUD**: Full CRUD lifecycle via CLI\n3. **TestCLI_WithRealCluster**: Test against real Kubernetes cluster\n4. **TestAdmin_Cleanup**: Cleanup with real orphaned resources\n5. **TestPicoD_HTTPServer**: PicoD HTTP server with various auth modes\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\n// pkg/cli/testutil/fixtures.go\npackage testutil\n\nimport (\n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\nfunc CreateTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Image: \"test-image:latest\",\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All 4 binaries build successfully (`agentd`, `picod`, `agentcube`, `agentcube-admin`)\n- [ ] `agentcube` CLI supports all CRUD operations for AgentRuntime\n- [ ] `agentcube` CLI supports all CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter\n- [ ] `agentcube` CLI supports exec/logs/describe commands\n- [ ] `agentcube-admin` CLI supports cleanup operations\n- [ ] `agentcube-admin` CLI supports diagnostics commands\n- [ ] All CLIs support multiple output formats (table, json, yaml)\n- [ ] All CLIs support kubeconfig and namespace flags\n- [ ] Shell completion scripts generated for bash/zsh/fish\n- [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass against real Kubernetes cluster\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples for all commands\n- [ ] Binaries are properly versioned with git commit info\n\n## References\n\n- AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n- AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n- `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n- `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n- `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n- Cobra CLI Framework: https://github.com/spf13/cobra\n- Kubernetes CLI Best Practices: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/cheatsheet/\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/agentd/main.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775863693239,"end":1775863693251}}}}
